# Conventional Commits

All commit messages must follow the Conventional Commits format.

## Format

```
<type>(<optional scope>): <short summary>

<optional body>

<optional footer>
```

- Summary: imperative mood, lower case, no trailing period, <= 72 chars.
- Leave a blank line before the body and before any footer.
- Use the body to explain the "why", not the "what".

## Allowed types

- `feat` - a new feature
- `fix` - a bug fix
- `docs` - documentation only (e.g. README, docs/)
- `style` - formatting/CSS/visual changes with no logic change
- `refactor` - code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
- `perf` - performance improvement
- `test` - adding or fixing tests
- `chore` - tooling, config, or maintenance
- `build` / `ci` - build system or CI changes

## Scope

Optional, lower case, project area. Examples for this game: `map`, `riddles`,
`gamestate`, `renderer`, `css`, `config`, `docs`.

## Breaking changes

Add `!` after the type/scope and a `BREAKING CHANGE:` footer.

## Examples

```
feat(renderer): reveal correct answer on the lose screen
fix(gamestate): pass original option index when answering
docs: record UX polish phase in changelog
style(css): enlarge answer buttons and add focus styles
chore(config): keep DEBUG_MODE false for final build
feat(config)!: rename MAP_VIEW_TIME_MS to MAP_VIEW_MS

BREAKING CHANGE: update references to the renamed config key.
```
